[DhtmlXQ_comment0]mg jieli am jnms g176||this is a very good example at how red can kill with the horse and cannon combination!||The beauty of this puzzle is in the way that red uses the horse to maneuver the cannon , and vice versa until the final kill.||Black is a few moves away for a checkmate. ||But how can red maneuver the horse and cannon for the checkmate?||||====||||Tactic: ||Maneuvering with Help from other Pieces||?? 01||||Maneuvering with help from other pieces ??||A very basic tactic.||Simply put, there are two (or maybe more ) pieces on the board, piece A and piece B. By moving piece B, you attack, clog, threaten to kill, threaten to capture...your opponent. He has to resolve this threat and you are allowed to move piece A to a better position. Very practical.||Commonly used tactics include maneuvering the chariot with the help of the cannon, maneuvering the horse with the help of the cannon etc. Often, a discovered check is used.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
